PLUS this thing is over 5DSMA which makes it extremely bullish still. Stocks over 5DSMA and pulling back to support are my bread and butter which is why I'm quadruple digits profit in the green with my 42 calls from earlier entry :)

Now if this was to gap down today at open and spike up into 41 Id be buying Puts expecting a rejection. Anyways, good luck with your trades. Bullish

Super simple HOD/LOD 30 min trading strategy: 
I typically like to go long after a red candle, go short after a weak green candle, on key levels of course. 
1. Rejection of previous HOD Puts 
2. Bullish over previous HOD + retest confirmation Calls 
3. Fakeout, no new high after red candle, no play 
4. 30 min wedge breakout at previous HOD, Calls
